@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Privacy Policy</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/css/Privacy.css">
</head>

<body>
    <div class="privacy-container">
        <h2 class="heading">Privacy Policy for Company.Codex</h2>
        <p class="introduction">
            At Company.Codex, we are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring the security of your personal
            information. This Privacy Policy outlines our practices concerning the collection, use, and protection of
            your data.
        </p>

        <div class="privacy-sections">
            <div class="card">
                <h3 class="section-heading">1. Information We Collect</h3>
                <p>We collect and process the following types of information:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Personal details such as name, age, and address</li>
                    <li>Contact information including email and phone number</li>
                    <li>Employment-related data such as salary and hiring date</li>
                    <li>User account information for system access</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <h3 class="section-heading">2. How We Use Your Information</h3>
                <p>Your information is used for:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Managing employee records and departmental structures</li>
                    <li>Facilitating internal communication</li>
                    <li>Ensuring proper system functionality and security</li>
                    <li>Complying with legal obligations</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <h3 class="section-heading">3. Data Protection</h3>
                <p>We implement robust security measures to protect your data from unauthorized access, alteration, or disclosure. This includes encryption, access controls, and regular security audits.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <h3 class="section-heading">4. Your Rights</h3>
                <p>You have the right to:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Access your personal data</li>
                    <li>Request corrections to your data</li>
                    <li>Request deletion of your data (where applicable)</li>
                    <li>Object to certain data processing activities</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <h3 class="section-heading">5. Updates to This Policy</h3>
                <p>We may update this policy periodically. Please check this page regularly for any changes.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

</body>

</html>
